The '''Rio de Janeiro train collision''' occurred on August 30, 2007 when two trains collided in the [[Nova Iguaçu]] suburb of [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]. Eleven people were killed.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/6971577.stm BBC News - Eight dead after Rio train crash]</ref>

The accident happened at 16:09 at a junction near Austin station in Nova Iguaçu in the region of [[Baixada Fluminense]] on the outskirts of Rio de Janeiro. A passenger train carrying 850 people collided with the back of an empty passenger train killing 8 people and injuring 111, 15 seriously.<ref>http://diariodonordeste.globo.com/materia.asp?codigo=465910 Choque de trens mata 8 e fere 111 no Rio</ref>

