'''Science-Power Module-1''' ('''SPM-1''', also known as '''NEM-1''') is a module scheduled to arrive at the [[international space station]] in 2022.<ref>https://ria.ru/space/20181119/1533093337.html</ref><ref name=russia-manifest>{{cite web |title=Russian Launch Manifest |url=http://www.sworld.com.au/steven/space/russia-man.txt |first=Steven |last=Pietrobon |date=28 March 2018 |access-date=28 March 2018}}</ref> It is going to dock to the [[Uzlovoy Module]], which is scheduled to be attached to the Nauka Module.<ref name=russia-manifest /> If [[Nauka (ISS module)|Nauka]] is canceled, then both the Uzlovoy module and NEM-1 would dock at the zenith port of [[Zvezda (ISS module)|Zvezda]]. SPM-1 is also a required component for the [[Orbital Piloted Assembly and Experiment Complex|OPSEK space station]]. The module is a new generation module which can replace the Zarya Functional Cargo Block (FGB) originally used in the [[TKS spacecraft]]<ref>http://www.russianspaceweb.com/nem.html</ref> which was the basis for the Zarya FGB module.

